\title{Quotient Group}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{definition}
\MML{group_6}{def 4}{K5}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]], let #{N\normalsubgroup G} be a [[gr-002P]] of #{G}. We define the \define{Quotient Group} #{G/N} to consist of [left cosets](gr-003H) of #{N} and the binary operator is given by
##{(gN)(hN)=(gh)N}
for any #{g,h\in G}. The inverse element of #{gN} is #{g^{-1}N}.}

\rmk{This is well-defined because [[gr-003N]].}